<paragraph blockId="5.[113,764,460,613]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">
<emphasis box="[151,208,461,484]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[244,475,460,484]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="longispina">
<emphasis box="[244,475,460,484]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Plagiochila longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a neotropical-montane species that is distinguished by more or less bluish stems, and leaves with numerous long-linear teeth all around the margins (
<bibRefCitation author="HEINRICHS, J. &amp; ANTON, I." box="[122,381,556,580]" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" pagination="109 - 111" refId="ref8339" refString="HEINRICHS, J., H. ANTON, I. HOLZ &amp; S. R. GRADSTEIN (2000). On the blue stem colour in Plagiochila longispina Lindenb. &amp; Gottsche (Plagiochilaceae). Cryptog., Bryol. 21: 109 - 111." type="journal article" year="2000">HEINRICHS et al., 2000</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[399,609,556,580]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="matanga">
<emphasis box="[399,609,556,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">Plagiochila matanga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[113,242,588,612]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Plagiochilaceae" genus="Plagiochila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Jungermanniales" pageId="5" pageNumber="46" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="longispina">
<emphasis box="[113,242,588,612]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="46">P. longispina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and a synonym.
</paragraph>
